## 13. Merge Strategy

The system must merge new information into the prior structured state.

### Example

Turn 1:

* “My left hand feels weak.”

Turn 2:

* “It started suddenly this morning.”

Turn 3:

* “My speech also sounds odd.”

The pipeline must **not** re-start from zero each time.
It must update the existing CaseState.

## Rule

The merge step should:

* keep old valid fields,
* replace unknown fields with new known values,
* allow correction if the user explicitly revises prior information.

### Correction example

Turn 1:

* “left hand”

Turn 2:

* “Actually it is the right hand.”

The merge logic must overwrite the prior position when the user clearly corrects it.

---

## 14. Minimal Context Policy

If recent messages are passed to the LLM, they must be minimal.

## Policy

* pass at most 2 recent turns,
* do not pass full transcript,
* do not use transcript when CaseState already contains the needed fact,
* prefer structured facts over old words.

### Good use case

Tone continuity and hesitation detection.

### Bad use case

Re-running symptom inference from the whole chat.

