## 17. Definition of Correct Behavior

The refactor is correct only if:

* the pipeline uses CaseState as the primary source of truth,
* the full conversation transcript is no longer required for core decisions,
* user corrections update structured state,
* concern estimation works across multiple turns,
* the system can still ask follow-up questions naturally,
* and token cost is reduced compared with full-history prompting.

